Share Trading CommissionShare Trading Commission
The share trading commission that will now be applied to share CFD positions is per industry standard. This commission will only apply to share CFDs and will not affect trading CFDs on Forex, Commodities, Indices, Crypto, Options and ETFs.
The share trading commission will be charged to your account balance at the opening and closing of positions on share CFDs and will be calculated as a percentage of the position value, or as a minimum amount, according to the instrument’s currency. If the commission percentage of the position value is less than the minimum amount, the minimum amount will apply. The commission percentage and minimum charge for each currency are available on our website.
Currency Conversion FeeCurrency Conversion Fee
Furthermore, we are now applying a new currency conversion fee for positions on instruments denominated in a currency different to the currency of your account, which will be up to 0.3% of a position's realised net profit and loss.
The fee will be reflected in real time into the unrealised net profit and loss of an open position and will be charged once the position is closed.
